text: Angelina Köhler (born 12 November 2000) is a German swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre butterfly at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. In 2018, she won the silver medal in the 100 m butterfly and the bronze medal in the 50 m butterfly event at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics in Buenos Aires, Argentina. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:German female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Female butterfly swimmers
